    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200\u00b0C/ 180\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 6 and boil a full kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice the <strong>brown onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Heat a large wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1/2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium-low heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced onions</strong> with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and cook for 10-12 min or until really softened</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-saag-with-spiced-roasted-tomatoes/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the onions are softening, add the <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> to a tray with the <strong>cumin seeds</strong> and<strong> chilli flakes </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Add 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> and give it a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 12-15 min or until the tomatoes are softened and starting to burst \u2013 these are your <strong>spiced roasted tomatoes</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-saag-with-spiced-roasted-tomatoes/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Dissolve the<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong> in 200ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [350ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Drain and rinse the <strong>green lentils</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-saag-with-spiced-roasted-tomatoes/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>spinach</strong> to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over it so that it starts to wilt</p><p>Rinse the<strong> wilted spinach</strong> under <strong>cold running water </strong>until it's cool</p><p>Once cool, squeeze the water out of the spinach as much as you can then chop it roughly</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-saag-with-spiced-roasted-tomatoes/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the onions have really softened, add the<strong> chopped ginger </strong>and <strong>garlic </strong>and cook for a further 1-2 min</p><p>Add the <strong>garam masala</strong>,<strong> tomato paste</strong>, <strong>chopped spinach</strong>,<strong> drained green lentils</strong> and<strong> vegetable stock </strong>and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Cook for 3-5 min or until the sauce has thickened and come together</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-saag-with-spiced-roasted-tomatoes/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the sauce is thickening, add the<strong> pittas </strong>to a baking tray and put the tray in the oven for 3-4 min or until warmed through</p><p>Strip the <strong>mint leaves </strong>from their stems and chop them finely, discard the stems</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-saag-with-spiced-roasted-tomatoes/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice the<strong> Greek cheese</strong> into cubes</p><p>Once the sauce has thickened, add the <strong>Greek cheese cubes</strong> and give it a gentle mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>lighter</strong> <strong>saag</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lighter-saag-with-spiced-roasted-tomatoes/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>lighter</strong> <strong>saag </strong>with the <strong>spiced roasted tomatoes</strong> and the <strong>warmed pitta </strong>to the side</p><p>Sprinkle the <strong>chopped mint</strong> over the<strong> </strong>spiced roasted tomatoes</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
